mirror-extension/
├── manifest.json              # Core extension config (permissions, injection capability, background flow)
├── background.js              # Listens for UI triggers, manages tracking, selectively injects scripts
├── popup.html                 # Extension dialog with checkboxes (response body, WebSocket) + start button
├── popup.js                   # Handles user selections and messaging to background
├── icons/
│   ├── icon16.png
│   ├── icon48.png
│   └── icon128.png
├── styles/
│   └── popup.css              # Optional stylesheet for popup UI refinement
├── utils/
│   └── captureHelpers.js      # Shared JS helpers (decode payloads, format logs, safety wrappers)
├── contentScripts/            # Gracefully injected observation modules (based on user toggles)
│   ├── wsMirror.js            # Mirrors WebSocket send/onmessage events
│   └── fetchMirror.js         # Mirrors fetch/XHR response bodies with page-level access
└── README.md                  # Optional: brief architecture notes and setup steps



Extension → Select options → Navigate
